##Learning Log Entry #1
I focused on learning how to fetch data from the iTunes Search API and then display artist results on the page
The most challenging part was understanding the JSON structure and also identifying which fields stood for different artist names and images
I practiced using fetch() and async/await to retrieve and log the data before rendering it. 

##Learning Log Entry #2
I created artist cards that included images and names of artists and organized them into a grid layout. 
One challenge I faced was connecting the search to the API call to ensure the results updated correctly each time. 
I also added loading and error messages to improve the overall user experience.

##Learning Log Entry #3
I focused on improving the design and interactivity of the app
I iterated the styling to make the app more visually appealing with better spacing, colors, and effects
I also handled edge cases such as empty searches and no results found. 
